<h3 class="wp-block-heading">History of Huobi</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.crunchbase.com/person/leon-li-2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Leon Li started Huobi</a>&nbsp;in 2013. He worked for Oracle before this. First, he got the Huobi domain and then began live Bitcoin trading. At first, the firm was based in China. But later, it moved to Seychelles because of rules in China.</p>



<p>The company grew quite fast. It opened offices in Hong Kong, South Korea, Japan and the United States too. The year 2023 was hard for Huobi as laws became stricter around crypto exchanges like it across many countries.</p>



<p>This led to job cuts where they had to let go of one-fifth of their staff.</p>



