<h3 class="wp-block-heading">KuCoin NFTs</h3>



<p>KuCoin offers a special feature called KuCoin NFTs. With KuCoin NFTs, you can invest in blue-chip NFT collections. But here&#8217;s the cool part: instead of owning the entire NFT, you can buy tradable tokens that represent fractions of an NFT.</p>



<p>These tokens are equal to 1/1,000,000 of the original NFT. This means that even if you don&#8217;t have a lot of money to spend on buying a whole NFT, you can still participate in this exciting market and potentially make some profits.</p>



<p>KuCoin has made it easier for people to access and invest in these valuable digital assets without breaking the bank.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">KuCoin Fees</h2>



<p>KuCoin charges trading fees for spot trading and futures trading. The fees vary based on the type of trade and the user&#8217;s VIP level.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Trading Fees</h3>



<p>Trading fees on KuCoin are extremely competitive when compared to other exchanges. This owes a lot to their tiered maker/taker fee model, which ranges from 0.005% to 0.1% based on the user&#8217;s tier level. In fact, holding KuCoin Shares can provide users with even more discounted trading fees of 0.1%. </p>



<p>KuCoin charges a flat fee of 0.10% per trade for most of its trading pairs. This makes KuCoin a cost-effective choice for both novice and experienced traders.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><th>Trading Type</th><th>Fees</th></tr><tr><td>KuCoin Maker/Taker Fee</td><td>0.005% to 0.1%</td></tr><tr><td>Discounted Trading Fees for KuCoin Share Holders</td><td>0.1%</td></tr><tr><td>Flat Fee for Most Trading Pairs</td><td>0.10%</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p>This table summarises the trading fees charged by KuCoin. From this, it&#8217;s clear that KuCoin offers excellent value with its low-cost fee structure. Whether you&#8217;re trading on a small or large scale, KuCoin can be a cost-effective solution for your cryptocurrency trading needs.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Spot Trading Fees</h3>



<p>KuCoin offers a competitive and low-cost fee structure for spot trading. It employs a maker taker fee structure, meaning that fees vary based on whether you are the maker (the one initiating the trade) or the taker (the one accepting the trade).</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><th>Role</th><th>Fees</th></tr><tr><td>Maker</td><td>0.1%</td></tr><tr><td>Taker</td><td>0.1%</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p>This base fee applies to all users irrespective of their trading volume. It is worth noting that this is a very competitive rate. Comparatively, Binance, another popular cryptocurrency exchange, also charges a fee of 0.1% for both makers and takers.</p>



<p>KuCoin also offers a tiered maker/taker fee structure. This means that your fees can go as low as 0.005% depending on your tier level.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><th>Tier Level</th><th>Maker Fee</th><th>Taker Fee</th></tr><tr><td>Tier 1</td><td>0.1%</td><td>0.1%</td></tr><tr><td>Tier 2</td><td>0.09%</td><td>0.09%</td></tr><tr><td>Tier 3</td><td>0.08%</td><td>0.08%</td></tr><tr><td>Tier 4</td><td>0.007%</td><td>0.007%</td></tr><tr><td>Tier 5</td><td>0.006%</td><td>0.006%</td></tr><tr><td>Tier 6</td><td>0.005%</td><td>0.005%</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p>In comparison, Bybit another competitor, charges a spot maker fee of 0.10% and a spot taker fee. By offering such competitive rates, KuCoin makes it more affordable for traders to buy and sell cryptocurrencies.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Futures Trading Fees</h3>



<p>KuCoin is well-known for its competitive futures trading fees. They use a tiered maker/taker fee model, which varies based on the trader&#8217;s trading volume and level. This fee structure allows for low costs for traders, particularly those with a high trading volume.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><th>Fee Level</th><th>30-day Trading Volume (BTC)</th><th>Maker Fee</th><th>Taker Fee</th></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>&lt; 50</td><td>0.02%</td><td>0.06%</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>≥ 50 &amp; &lt; 200</td><td>0.015%</td><td>0.06%</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>≥ 200 &amp; &lt; 500</td><td>0.01%</td><td>0.06%</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>≥ 500 &amp; &lt; 1200</td><td>0.005%</td><td>0.06%</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>≥ 1200 &amp; &lt; 2000</td><td>-0.005%</td><td>0.06%</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>≥ 2000</td><td>-0.01%</td><td>0.06%</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p>This table showcases the fee levels and corresponding maker and taker fees on KuCoin. As you can see, the lowest available maker fee on KuCoin for futures trading is -0.01%, an attractive feature for high-frequency traders. Furthermore, compared to the industry average, KuCoin offers relatively low futures trading fees starting from 0.02% for makers and 0.06% for takers, making it a cost-effective choice for traders.</p>



