<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Uphold Security</h3>



<p>Uphold puts your safety first. They guard your money and data with strong encryption. The platform has many defenses against attacks. Uphold staff have passed hard checks and use two-factor authentication for added security.</p>



<p>They work hard to keep the chance of attacks very low. The crypto exchange makes sure to keep its users and their cash safe at all times.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Uphold Card</h3>



<p>You can use the Uphold Card both online and at physical stores. It works with Apple Pay and Google Pay too. This card lets you spend your crypto on everyday things. There is a one-time fee of $9.95 for the card and each cash out costs $2.50.</p>



<p>The most money you can take out in a day is $1,500, but only up to $500 per time. An extra perk is that when using this card, you get cash back rewards as cryptocurrencies.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Uphold Fees</h2>



<p>Uphold charges fees for using their platform. One type of fee is called a spread fee, which is charged on every cryptocurrency trade you make. The amount of the spread fee varies depending on the specific cryptocurrency you are buying or selling.</p>



<p>It can range from 0.2% to 3% of the transaction amount.</p>



<p>In addition to the spread fee, there is also a transaction fee for any transactions below $100 in value. This fee is set at $0.99 per transaction.</p>



<p>If you choose to deposit funds into your Uphold account using a credit or debit card, there is a 3.99% fee per deposit.</p>



<p>It&#8217;s important to be aware of these fees when using Uphold so that you can factor them into your trading decisions and budget accordingly.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Using Uphold</h2>



